TITLE: Leaked Pentagon documents claim Israel’s Mossad encouraged protests against Netanyahu
SUMMARY: Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu and the Mossad denied reports Sunday that Israel's intelligence agency had encouraged protests against Netanyahu's judicial reform efforts.

TITLE: Religious liberty nonprofit blasts bill banning protests near drag shows: 'Deranged parody of public law'
SUMMARY: Liberty Coalition Canada founder Michael Thiessen blasted a recent provincial bill in Ontario that would criminalize protests and "offensive remarks" around drag shows.

TITLE: Building in Marseille, France, collapses after explosion, multiple people believed trapped under rubble
SUMMARY: The desperate search for victims continued Sunday in Marseille, France, after an explosion collapsed a residential building and caused a fire to burn underneath the rubble.

TITLE: Israeli military: 3 rockets fired from Syria toward Israel
SUMMARY: Jews, Christians, and Muslims alike flock to Israel each spring for Easter, Passover, and Ramadan. This year, violence is part and parcel of worship.

TITLE: Ben Ferencz, last living Nuremberg prosecutor of Nazis, dies
SUMMARY: An internationally-recognized leader during and after the second World War, Ferencz went above and beyond the call of duty to restore dignity to Jewish peoples.

TITLE: China called out by World Health Organization over COVID origin data
SUMMARY: Chinese health officials are defending their efforts to find the source of the coronavirus pandemic after a World Health Organization leader said it should have shared data much sooner.

TITLE: United Kingdom still negotiating with Taliban for three Brits in custody, including 'danger tourist'
SUMMARY: The Taliban allegedly have three British nationals in custody, one of whom has not been named, and the British government has not said how far into discussions they have gone.

TITLE: Spanish TV star reveals adopted surrogate baby belongs to her deceased son: report
SUMMARY: The European Union generally has ruled commercial surrogate pregnancies illegal, and Ana Obregón's decision to seek one caused a firestorm debate in Spain.

TITLE: McCaul says China saber-rattling will 'only firm up our resolve' amid aggression against Taiwan
SUMMARY: The bipartisan delegation affirmed its commitment to support Taiwan's deterrence efforts, stressing the need to protect the island's semconductor production.

TITLE: New exhibit in Mexico City celebrates discovery of Mexica lunar goddess monolith
SUMMARY: Mexico City’s Museum of Templo Mayor is hosting a new exhibit celebrating the discovery of a monolith depicting the Mexica lunar goddess Coyolxauhqui.

TITLE: China sends fighter jets toward Taiwan after Tsai's US meeting
SUMMARY: China sent warships and dozens of fighter jets toward Taiwan on Saturday following a meeting between House Speaker Kevin McCarthy and Taiwanese President Tsai Ing-wen.

TITLE: North Korea claims successful test of underwater nuclear-capable drone
SUMMARY: North Korean media released images this week that regime officials claim show testing of a nuclear-capable underwater weapons system.

TITLE: Over 100K Canadians without power after brutal ice storm
SUMMARY: Hundreds of thousands of Canadians were left without power in parts of Quebec and Ontario after the Great White North's eastern half was hit with a major ice storm.

TITLE: Explosion reported at Iraqi airport at center of Kurdish conflict
SUMMARY: An explosion reportedly struck next to northern Iraq's Suleimaniyah International Airport, located in Kurdish territory embroiled in conflict.

TITLE: 3 killed in Northern Italy after car crashes into farm silo
SUMMARY: Three people were killed in Northern Italy after a car crashed into a farm silo that collapsed on the vehicle. The farm breeds over two million chickens per year.

TITLE: FBI turns to social media to recruit Russians for intelligence gathering
SUMMARY: The FBI has turned to social media to help it ramp up its Russian recruitment and intelligence gathering.

TITLE: Israel terror attack in Tel Aviv leaves three dead, multiple injured after car rams into crowd
SUMMARY: Authorities in Israel say that an attack in Tel Aviv has left several people injured after a car rammed into a group of people on Friday.

TITLE: 6 men given life sentences in Congo for killing of Italian ambassador
SUMMARY: Six men were given life sentences in Congo for the 2021 killing of Italy's ambassador. Eastern Congo armed groups have been fighting for decades.

TITLE: Former Belarusian opposition leader gets 17-year sentence in absentia
SUMMARY: Belarusian opposition leader Valery Tsepkalo was sentenced in absentia to 17 years in prison on charges of extremism and "discrediting Belarus," among others.

TITLE: Wall Street Journal reporter charged with spying in Russia, an accusation he denies
SUMMARY: Wall Street Journal reporter Evan Gershkovich is denying formal espionage charges that have been filed against him, Russian state media is reporting.

TITLE: Conflict with China 'last resort' but Congress will authorize troops if Americans support it: McCaul
SUMMARY: Although it would be a "last resort," Congress would approve boots on the ground following an attack on Taiwan should Americans support the move, Rep. Michael McCaul told Fox News.

TITLE: Filipinos nailed to crosses in reenactment of Christ’s crucifiction, despite Church's objection
SUMMARY: Several Filipinos were nailed to crosses on Good Friday despite objections from Catholic Church leaders, who said people can show their devotion without hurting themselves.

TITLE: South Korea, Japan, US call for more support to curb North Korea’s growing nuclear arsenal
SUMMARY: Japan, South Korea, and the U.S. are calling for more international support to stop North Korea from acquiring more resources for its nuclear program.

TITLE: 200 firefighters in Mexico City battle huge blaze at wholesale market
SUMMARY: Hundreds of firefighters arrived at a market that was lit in a huge blaze in Mexico City. No injuries were reported and most of the fire was under control within several hours.

TITLE: Pope Francis to miss Good Friday Way of the Cross procession due to low temperatures
SUMMARY: Pope Francis will not preside over the Way of the Cross event on Good Friday due to freezing weather in Rome. Francis will watch from his home in the Vatican.
